HEADWORD: oriented
<hw>oriented</hw></mhw> <pos>adj.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Adjusted or aligned to surroundings or circumstances;
sometimes used in combination; <as>as, to get <ex>oriented</ex> on one's
first day at a new job</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>headed or intending to head in a certain direction;
<as>as, college-<ex>oriented</ex> students</as>. Opposite of
<ant>unoriented</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> directed, minded.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>orienting</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>orientating</ent>⟦br⟧
